.TH "smsm_update_bits" 9 "smsm_update_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smsm_update_bits \- change bit in outgoing entry and inform subscribers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" smsm_update_bits
.BI "(void *data "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "u32 value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
smsm context pointer
.IP "mask" 12
value mask
.IP "value" 12
new value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used to set and clear the bits in the outgoing/local entry and inform
subscribers about the change.
